<seg id="223">Conduct of the auditing operation</seg>
<seg id="224">As part of the preparation of the parallel auditing operations, in the first half of July 2005, a coordination meeting took place between representatives of the SAO, the Czech Republic and representatives of the SAO of the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="225">The participants of this meeting became acquainted with the VAT legislation in both countries and with the integration of the VIES electronic system into the national databases.</seg>
<seg id="226">The outcome of the meeting was the specification of the scope of cooperation and the setting of conditions for the selection of the auditing samples.</seg>
<seg id="227">Both parties agreed that the cooperation will focus on the following areas: (a) verification of the validity and correctness of the VAT numbers of persons registered for VAT in the Czech Republic or Slovakia in intra-community supplies; (b) verification of data on intra-community acquisitions listed in the DAP by payers in the Czech Republic using information from the summary reports (hereinafter referred to as "SH") of payers from the Slovak Republic contained in the VIES system, and vice versa; (c) exchange of information between tax administrations in the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic on executed commercial transactions.</seg>
<seg id="228">Furthermore, it was agreed that the selection of tax entities for inspection will be carried out in relation to the volume of intra-community supplies between the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic and according to the number of requests for international cooperation sent and received between the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic by means of the SCAC form.</seg>
<seg id="229">5.1 Intra-community transactions</seg>
<seg id="230">The procedure of information processing by tax administrations of the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic in intra-community supplies and acquisitions of goods is illustrated by the following diagram.</seg>
<seg id="231">5.1.1 Intra-community supplies</seg>
<seg id="232">If the VAT payer makes an intra-community delivery, he is obliged to submit SH by the 25th day after the end of the calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="233">The payer in the Czech Republic provides in the SH summary information on his/her deliveries of goods to another EU Member State exempt from VAT for the previous calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="234">The payer in SR is obliged to enter in the SH the value of goods that were tax exempt and delivered from the territory of the country to other EU Member States for the period of the calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="235">Data on the value of the goods supplied are always given in the SH in Czech or Slovak currency, broken down by individual tax entities with an indication of their VAT number under which they were registered in their country.</seg>
<seg id="236">Data on services shall not be included in the SH.</seg>
<seg id="237">If the payer in the Czech Republic finds out that he has given incorrect data in the SH, he is obliged to file a subsequent SH.</seg>
<seg id="238">If the payer in SR finds that the data given in the SH were incomplete or incorrect, he shall file a corrective SH before the deadline for filing the SH, after the expiry of this deadline he shall file an additional SH.</seg>
<seg id="239">The VIES system allows the exchange of information on the registration data of VAT-registered payers in the EU Member States.</seg>
<seg id="240">Taxpayers from the Czech Republic or Slovakia can verify whether the tax ID of the respective acquirer is registered in the given EU Member State.</seg>
<seg id="241">Data from the submitted SH are grouped on the MF CLO or DR CLO by the VIES system according to the individual tax ID of the acquirer.</seg>
<seg id="242">The aggregate value of all deliveries for each tax ID of the acquirer and the code of the method of delivery from all its Czech or Slovak suppliers, the so-called L1QD files, are created.</seg>
<seg id="243">Data from the L1QD files are sent to the respective EU Member States no later than three months after the end of the quarter to which the data relate.</seg>
<seg id="244">The total value of intra-Community deliveries between the Czech Republic and Slovakia (from the L1QD files) is given in the following table.</seg>
<seg id="245">If the VIES system in another Member State finds the erroneous tax ID of the acquirer in the sent L1QD files, it generates the so-called O_MCTL report, which contains all the erroneous tax ID with an indication of the type of error.</seg>
<seg id="246">This report is then sent to the MF CLO or DR CLO.</seg>
<seg id="247">The O_MCTL report may contain 4 types of errors: formally erroneous VAT numbers, the VAT numbers are not registered in the given state or have never been allocated, the acquirer with a specific VAT number was not a VAT payer in the given quarter, the registration for the VAT of the acquirer was terminated during the quarter.</seg>
<seg id="248">In the CR, the MF CLO transmits the data from the received O_MCTL reports to the tax authorities.</seg>
