<seg id="278">5.1.2 Intra-Community acquisitions</seg>
<seg id="279">The VIES system provides information on the values of intra-community transactions carried out within EU Member States.</seg>
<seg id="280">Acquisition of goods in the Czech Republic</seg>
<seg id="281">In the Czech Republic, the delivered SH data submitted by payers from other EU Member States (delivered L1QD) are processed by MF CLO.</seg>
<seg id="282">During processing, the data are converted at the minimum and maximum daily exchange rates of the Czech National Bank for the respective period and then compared with the acquisition value stated by Czech payers in the DAP for the respective quarter.</seg>
<seg id="283">The value of acquisitions of goods reported by payers in the DAP should be in the range of the minimum and maximum converted L1QD values (values L1min and L1max).</seg>
<seg id="284">If the value reported in the DAP is lower than the value L1min, a so-called verification order is generated for payers with the most significant irregularities.</seg>
<seg id="285">The orders for verification of acquisitions of goods are a warning of problematic tax entities and are transmitted to the locally relevant financial authorities, which must investigate the transmitted data.</seg>
