<seg id="287">The SAO, CR found that in 33 cases the audited tax authorities did not verify irregularities in the values of intra-community acquisitions, which were indicated by the received verification orders.</seg>
<seg id="288">The total difference between the values stated in the SH of payers from other EU Member States and the DAP of Czech payers in these cases amounted to at least CZK 148,319,000.</seg>
<seg id="289">The SAO, CR selected for the audit 533 files of tax entities for which the audited tax authorities received a verification order from the Ministry of Finance.</seg>
<seg id="290">The audit found the following most frequent causes of differences between the values stated in the DAP of the acquirer and in the SH of the supplier: on the side of the acquirer (Czech payer) in 263 cases the acquirer did not state the acquisition of goods in the regular DAP, in 93 cases the payer declared the acquisition of goods in a different tax period than in which it was obliged to declare the tax, in 6 cases the acquirer stated the value of the acquired goods in the incorrect DAP line, on the side of the supplier (EU payer) in 88 cases the EU payers included in their SH the values of the provided services to the Czech payer, of which in 54 cases the Slovak payer was involved, in 39 cases the suppliers included in the SH the delivery of goods in a different tax period than the Czech acquirers in their DAP, in 22 cases the suppliers stated in the SH the incorrect VAT number of the Czech payer, in 16 cases the suppliers stated in the SH the wrong values of the delivery of goods, in 12 cases the suppliers included in the SH the value of goods delivered to the CR before 1.5.2004, in 5 cases the suppliers included in the SH the value of received advances.</seg>
<seg id="291">On the side of the payers from the Slovak Republic, the value of provided services was included in the SH most frequently.</seg>
<seg id="292">In the audited financial offices, 54 such cases were found.</seg>
