<seg id="310">Acquisition of goods in the Slovak Republic</seg>
<seg id="311">In the Slovak Republic, the APV DIS system allows comparing data on the value of the acquired goods obtained through the VIES system from other EU Member States with the data listed in the Slovak acquirers' DAP.</seg>
<seg id="312">The method by which the data are compared is called the "MIN-MAX method".</seg>
<seg id="313">Using this method, the values of supplies of goods listed in the SH of payers from other EU Member States are converted at the minimum and maximum exchange rates for the respective quarter.</seg>
<seg id="314">The MIN-MAX interval is created, which is used for comparison with the values of acquisitions of goods listed in the DAP of Slovak payers.</seg>
<seg id="315">The DR CLO sends the tax administrators information on the values of intra-community acquisitions listed in the DAP and the values of supplies from the EU in the VIES system.</seg>
<seg id="316">The tax administrator decides which persons registered for VAT will be checked for the difference, taking also into account other risk analysis criteria.</seg>
<seg id="317">On the basis of the data provided by the DR CLO, the SAO SR selected 57 files of Slovak acquirers of goods from the audited tax authorities, of which 25 payers acquired goods from the Czech Republic, where the highest differences between the acquisition values obtained from the VIES system and the values declared in the DAP were found.</seg>
