<seg id="153">In some cases, this was an extension of more than one year and the proceedings were not completed at the time of the inspection.</seg>
<seg id="154">Some benefit in shortening the asylum procedure is expected from the establishment of joint offices of the Ministry of Agriculture and the Úrad hraničnej a cudzineckej polície Policajného zboru in reception centres in Adamova-Gbeloch, Opatovskej Novej Vsi and Liptovské Vlachoch, which was joined at the time of the inspection from 1.10.2004.</seg>
<seg id="155">This is supposed to simplify the procedures and shorten the time limits of the proceedings between the two parts of the asylum process.</seg>
<seg id="156">5. Asylum facilities</seg>
<seg id="157">The Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic established asylum facilities in which they gradually created suitable conditions for providing services to participants in the asylum procedure.</seg>
<seg id="158">The asylum facilities provide asylum seekers with accommodation, meals, health care, pocket money and basic material equipment and sanitary needs during their stay.</seg>
<seg id="159">At the same time, courses are organized as part of leisure activities and the applicants are created conditions for cultural and sports activities.</seg>
<seg id="160">5.1 Asylum facilities in the Czech Republic</seg>
<seg id="161">SUZ manages and operates asylum facilities and is responsible for managing the state's property in the premises of the reception centre Vyšní Lhota, the reception and residence centre Červený Újezd, the residential centres Bělá-Jezová, Zastávka u Brna, Kostelec nad Orlicí, Havířov and in the premises of the integration asylum centres Jaroměř and Zastávka u Brna.</seg>
<seg id="162">At the beginning of 2002, a reception centre was established in the transit area of Prague-Ruzyně airport.</seg>
<seg id="163">SUZ also operates asylum facilities in Stráž pod Ralskem, Seč, Bruntál, Zbýšov and Kašava, which are operated by a legal entity on the basis of § 80 paragraph 3 of Act No 325/1999 Coll. on Asylum.</seg>
<seg id="164">The total accommodation capacity of the reception centres is 747 places and the total accommodation capacity of the accommodation centres is 1 977 places.</seg>
<seg id="165">Reception centres are closed facilities that asylum seekers are not allowed to leave until the prescribed medical examinations and basic reception operations referred to in Act No 325/1999 Coll., on Asylum have been carried out.</seg>
<seg id="166">Infringement of the obligation to stay in the reception centre is classified as an offence.</seg>
<seg id="167">The accommodation centres to which asylum seekers come from reception centres are used for housing asylum seekers until the decision on their application to grant or not to grant asylum becomes final.</seg>
<seg id="168">Under certain conditions, asylum seekers have the possibility to leave the accommodation centres or to stay in private.</seg>
<seg id="169">Asylum seekers have the right to free accommodation, provision of meals, other services and pocket money in the reception and accommodation centres in which they are reported to be staying, provided that they have suffered the acts necessary to establish their financial and financial circumstances, and these conditions are such that even partial reimbursement of the said services cannot be fairly claimed from them.</seg>
<seg id="170">Integration asylum centres are used for the temporary accommodation of persons who have been granted asylum.</seg>
<seg id="171">Clients are accommodated in the centre on the basis of an accommodation contract, which is usually concluded for 6 months, with the possibility of extension until adequate housing can be provided for them, or they can provide it themselves within the framework of the state integration programme.</seg>
<seg id="172">In the integration centre, clients cover all the costs of accommodation and eat individually.</seg>
<seg id="173">Persons with recognised refugee status have the same rights and obligations as Czech citizens and have the same access to social security.</seg>
<seg id="174">5.1.1 Costs of asylum facilities</seg>
<seg id="175">For the comparison of asylum facilities, the cost per physical stay day was chosen as the best indicator.</seg>
<seg id="176">It is based on the actual number of persons who were actually provided with services provided by the asylum facility each day.</seg>
