<seg id="178">The cost per stay day in the own asylum facility operated by SUZ decreases with the increasing load capacity of these facilities. This is due to the fact that the fixed costs of running the facilities are allocated to more asylum seekers.</seg>
<seg id="179">The total cost of providing services for asylum seekers increases proportionately with their increasing number.</seg>
<seg id="180">In 2001 and 2003, the own asylum facilities accommodated applicants in crisis capacity.</seg>
<seg id="181">In part of 2003, extra accommodation capacity in residential containers (320 beds in total) was even used to address the capacity crisis of asylum facilities caused by the mass arrival of asylum seekers of Chechen nationality from Poland.</seg>
