<seg id="951">During the audited period, the amount of expenditure related to the upgrade of the EMCS system in the Slovak Republic in terms of one transport was 2.3 times higher than the expenditure of the same type in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="952">Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="953">The cooperation of the SAO of the Czech Republic and the SAO of the Slovak Republic fulfilled the objectives.</seg>
<seg id="954">Both audit institutions gained a deeper knowledge of the excise tax administration system in the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="955">It was found that despite the common basic legal framework, there are significant differences in both tax systems that affect the efficiency of the excise tax administration.</seg>
<seg id="956">During parallel audits, examples of good practice were found that could contribute to the reduction of tax fraud, their importance will increase with increasing tax rates.</seg>
<seg id="957">Procedures reducing the costs of the excise tax administration were also identified.</seg>
<seg id="958">Mutual cooperation has revealed differences that significantly affect the efficiency of tax administration and limit international comparisons, unless mutually coordinated due diligence checks are carried out with the tax administration.</seg>
<seg id="959">In this, the role of supreme audit institutions is irreplaceable.</seg>
