<seg id="127">The Czech Ministry of Finance has not yet proposed a change in the provision introducing an obligation for tax administrators to cancel VAT registration for payers in case of repeated failure to file a VAT return.</seg>
<seg id="128">According to the VAT Act, the tax administrator can cancel a tax payer's registration "ex offo" in cases where: (a) the payer did not perform a performance for twelve consecutive months without notifying the tax administrator of the reason; (b) the payer does not comply with his obligations arising from this Act; (c) the payer ceases to be a taxable person.</seg>
