<seg id="482">4.4.4 Comparison and evaluation</seg>
<seg id="483">In the area of international assistance for recovery of claims, all EU Member States are governed by the same European legislation.</seg>
<seg id="484">Therefore, the way in which requests for international assistance for recovery of claims are handled is the same in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="485">The SAO and the BRH compared the statistics submitted by both Member States to the European Commission for the period 2006-2008.</seg>
<seg id="486">The data contained in these statistics did not match.</seg>
<seg id="487">In the 2006 report, the European Commission recommended that Member States pay increased attention to the management of their statistics.</seg>
<seg id="488">In the 2009 report, the Commission concluded that the incidence of inconsistencies in the statistics has decreased, even though the number of requests has increased.</seg>
<seg id="489">Both SAIs consider it important that statistical issues are discussed again at EU level.</seg>
<seg id="490">This discussion should focus on how to avoid persistent inconsistencies, otherwise the data reported by individual EU States in the statistics will not be reliable and comparable.</seg>
<seg id="491">In addition, both SAIs agree that reliable statistics should report the annual number of requests as well as the nature of the claims in question (i.e. whether the claims relate to VAT, income tax, etc.) as well as the amount of claims recovered by individual Member States.</seg>
<seg id="492">Both SAIs consider it important for the Commission to provide more detailed analyses of the statistics submitted by the Member States, as this may assist Member States in assessing their own effectiveness in fighting VAT fraud.</seg>
<seg id="493">The fact that the recovery rate can be calculated broken down by Member State, both SAIs consider it useful for Member States with lower recovery rates to step up their efforts and try to improve the recovery rate at least to the level of the EU average.</seg>
<seg id="494">If a Member State so wishes, the Commission should actively participate in this process.</seg>
<seg id="495">In particular, in 2006 and 2007, the Czech Ministry of Finance did not submit requests for recovery of claims on time to the local tax authorities.</seg>
